{{Quote|The problem might be that you're reaching a little too high. Aim for the middle and you'll never miss. Right? I think you got a good heart, I believe what you're saying. But not everybody's the world-saving type. I'm not, and I'm happy. Right? I found my place.|Happy Hogan to [[Wade Wilson]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
'''Harold Joseph "Happy" Hogan''' is the Head of Security of [[Stark Industries]], and was one of [[Tony Stark]]'s closest friends. A former boxer, he was employed by Stark as a personal chauffeur and bodyguard and assisted him in taking down [[Ivan Vanko]]. Hogan was [[Destruction of the Chinese Theatre|almost killed]] during [[Aldrich Killian]]'s [[Aldrich Killian's False Flag Attacks|war]], which motivated Stark to seek out the [[Trevor Slattery|Mandarin]], who he believed was behind Hogan's injuries. After his recovery, Hogan continued to serve as Stark's friend and employee.

Hogan oversaw Stark's mentorship over [[Peter Parker]] as [[Spider-Man]], aiding the young hero on his trip to [[Germany]] and acting as their liaison when Parker continued his superhero activities. Initially irritated by the boy and avoiding him, Hogan grew to respect Parker when he delivered [[Vulture]] to justice, as he targeted a cargo plane under Hogan's direct supervision that was carrying equipment for the [[Avengers Compound]].

In [[2023]], Hogan was present at Stark's funeral. The [[2024|following year]], he helped Spider-Man deal with [[Mysterio]] and the [[Elementals]] in [[Europe]]. When Parker became victim to public hostility after he was framed for murdering Mysterio, Hogan allowed him and May to use his [[Happy Hogan's Condominium|condo]]. Hogan also hired [[Matt Murdock]] to defend him after he was investigated by [[Damage Control]] due to the Stark Industries [[Stark Industries Combat Drones|drones]] used during the [[Battle of London]]. Later, Hogan was ridden with grief by May's murder and had his memories of Parker erased by [[Doctor Strange]].

==Biography==
{{MD|Harold Hogan (Earth-199999)}}
===Tony Stark's Bodyguard===
====Employed by Tony Stark====
{{Quote|[[Tony Stark|Tony]] was my best friend.|Happy Hogan to [[Peter Parker]]|Spider-Man: Far From Home}}
Harold Hogan was a former boxer who was hired by [[Tony Stark]] to be his personal chauffeur and bodyguard after his boxing career ended.<ref>''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xxuydthoPiM I Am Iron Man: Behind the Scenes Making of Iron Man]''</ref> Stark gave him the nickname of "Happy" due to his typically glum personality.{{Ref|MSCE}}

====New Year's in Switzerland====
{{Quote|I gave a speech? How was it?"<br>"Edifying."<br>"Unintelligible."<br>"Really? It's my favorite kind, a winning combo.|[[Tony Stark]], Happy Hogan and [[Maya Hansen]]|Iron Man 3}}
[[File:Happy-Hogan-Bern-Tony-Stark.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Happy Hogan in Bern along with [[Tony Stark]]]]
On New Year's Eve in [[1999]], Hogan accompanied Stark to [[Bern]], [[Switzerland]] on his first and only date with [[Maya Hansen]]. Hogan stayed with Stark as he made his way through the party after the [[Bern 2000]], being introduced to [[Ho Yinsen]] and Doctor [[Wu]]. When they made it to the elevator, Hogan tried and failed to keep an eccentric scientist named [[Aldrich Killian]] away from Stark and Hansen as he attempted to gain Stark's investment for [[A.I.M.]]
[[File:Happy-Hogan-IM3-Goatee.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan speaks to [[Tony Stark|Stark]] and [[Maya Hansen]]]]
Hogan escorted Stark and Hansen back to her hotel room, where they discussed her experiments with a [[Extremis|virus]] which would allow the human body to instantly regenerate damaged tissue, even severed limbs. Hogan was skeptical and fiddled with an experimental plant, breaking off a stem. As he prepared to leave, the plant exploded, causing Hogan to instinctively react by jumping on Stark to protect him. When the situation was explained, Hogan wished Stark and Hansen a Happy New Year before leaving them alone for the night.{{Ref|IM3}}

====[[Kidnapping of Tony Stark]]====
[[File:HappyHogan-FirstScene-IM.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan and [[Tony Stark]] enjoy some gambling]]
{{Quote|I thought I lost you back there!"<br>"You did, sir.|[[Tony Stark]] and Happy Hogan|Iron Man (film)}}
In [[2008]], Hogan accompanied Stark to [[Caesars Palace]] in [[Las Vegas]] for an awards ceremony, although Stark decided not to attend and instead spent his time gambling and flirting with the girls in the club. They were interrupted by Stark's friend [[James Rhodes]] who handed Stark his award and berated him for missing the ceremony. As they exited the casino, they were stopped by [[Christine Everhart]] who interviewed Stark about his company. Stark charmed Everhart and Hogan drove them both back to his [[Tony Stark's Mansion|mansion]].
[[File:Tony Stark and Happy Hogan.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan escorts [[Tony Stark]] to his [[Stark Industries Private Jet|private jet]]]]
The next morning, Hogan followed Stark to the [[Stark Industries Aviation Division]] in a {{WPS|Rolls Royce Phantom VII}}, but had trouble keeping up with him as Stark drove the faster {{WPS|Audi R8#First generation (2006–2015: Type 42)|Audi R8}}. Stark flew to [[Afghanistan]] where he demonstrated the [[Jericho]] before being kidnapped by the terrorist organization [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]. Three months later, Stark was found walking across the desert by [[James Rhodes]], having escaped from the Ten Rings himself.
[[File:Ironman 2430.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan waits for [[Tony Stark]]]]
Upon Stark's return to the [[United States of America]], Hogan drove [[Pepper Potts]] to the airport to meet Stark and then drove them back to [[Stark Industries]] to meet [[Obadiah Stane]], after stopping to get cheeseburgers for Stark per his request. Hogan was present when Stark gave a press conference about his experience, where he also announced he would be shutting down the weapons manufacturing section of Stark Industries.{{Ref|IM}}

====Protecting Iron Man====
[[File:Happy-Hogan-Tony-Stark-Expo.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan and Stark leave the [[Stark Expo]]]]
{{Quote|Look what we got here, the new model."<br>"Hey, does [[U.S. Marshal|she]] come with the car?"<br>"I certainly hope so.|Happy Hogan and [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man 2}}
With [[Tony Stark]] having admitted to being the superhero [[Iron Man]], Hogan's job became more difficult as Stark gained mass popularity, and developed a vast fan following. After a [[Stark Expo]] presentation, Hogan escorted Stark through the sea of people looking to gain his attention whilst introducing figures of interest. When the pair finally made it outside, they found a beautiful [[U.S. Marshal]] waiting for them. She informed Stark that he had been issued a subpoena to appear in [[Washington, D.C.]] before a [[United States Congress|U.S. Congressional]] committee headed by Senator [[Stern]]. Hogan took the subpoena and drove them to D.C.{{Ref|IM2}}

====Boxing Training====
[[File:Happy-Hogan-Boxing.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan boxes with [[Tony Stark]]]]
{{Quote|What the hell was that?!"<br>"It's called mixed martial arts, it's been around for three weeks."<br>"It's called dirty boxing, there's nothing new about it.|Happy Hogan and [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man 2}}
Hogan continued to work closely with [[Tony Stark]] and the two developed a close friendship. They often boxed together to keep fit, although Stark would often cheat during their fights, using mixed martial arts (MMA) techniques to elbow Hogan in the face or kick him in the chest, much to his annoyance.
[[File:Happy-Hogan-Boxing-Rushman.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan attempts to train [[Natasha Romanoff|Natalie Rushman]]]]
One day while training, they were interrupted by [[Natasha Romanoff|Natalie Rushman]], a legal representative from [[Stark Industries]] as [[Pepper Potts]] had been promoted to CEO. Stark asked Hogan to show Rushman how to box; he agreed and teased her about the unlikelihood of her having any real training. However, Hogan quickly learned that Rushman was more than she seemed when she effortlessly blocked a punch and threw him painfully to the floor in a scissoring technique, to which Stark mocked Hogan.{{Ref|IM2}}

====[[Duel of Monaco]]====
[[File:Happy Hogan Guarding Mark V.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan with the [[Iron Man Armor: Mark V|Mark V suitcase armor]]]]
{{Quote|Are you okay?!"<br>"Yeah. Were you headed for me or [[Whiplash|him]]?"<br>"I was trying to scare him!"<br>"Because I can't tell!|Happy Hogan and [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man 2}}
During the [[Circuit de Monaco]], Hogan accompanied [[Tony Stark]], [[Pepper Potts]] and [[Natasha Romanoff|Natalie Rushman]], keeping the [[Iron Man Armor: Mark V|Mark V suitcase armor]] handcuffed to his wrist. When Stark entered the race himself, taking over his own formula one racing car, he was soon attacked by terrorist [[Ivan Vanko]], using a recreated [[Arc Reactor]]-powered [[Whiplash Armor: Mark I|suit with electric whips]]. Hogan risked his life in trying to get the Suitcase Armor to Stark, driving into the race one-handed while Potts unlocked its handcuff.
[[File:Happy-Hogan-saves-Tony-Stark-IM2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan saves [[Tony Stark]] from [[Ivan Vanko]]]]
Hogan drove down the wrong way of the track and slammed Vanko against the fencing. Stark yelled at Hogan for nearly hitting him in the crash and tried to enter the car. However, Vanko recovered and attacked the car with his whips, ripping it apart and nearly hitting Hogan and Potts. They managed to give Stark the armor and he was able to use it to defeat Vanko after a brief but brutal [[Duel of Monaco|fight]]. Hogan and Potts then watched as Vanko was taken away by the police, taunting Stark that he had lost.{{Ref|IM2}}

====Trouble Continues====
[[File:Happy-Hogan-runs-into-fight.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan rescues [[Pepper Potts]]]]
[[Tony Stark]] hosted a birthday party in his [[Tony Stark's Mansion|Mansion]], proceeding to get drunk and wear [[Iron Man Armor: Mark IV|one of his Iron Man suits]] to impress his guests. This action angered [[James Rhodes]], who had been defending Stark to the government, so he put on [[Iron Man Armor: Mark II|another suit]] and confronted Stark. The two friends began [[Duel at Tony Stark's Mansion|fighting]] throughout the Mansion and when the destruction neared [[Pepper Potts]], Hogan quickly ran inside to pull her to safety. The duel ended with great damage to the mansion and Rhodes leaving with the Iron Man suit.
[[File:Happy-Hogan-Potts-Office.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan in [[Pepper Potts]]' office]]
Back at [[Stark Industries]] the next day, Hogan went to collect Potts for her upcoming meeting and found her talking with Stark. He asked if Potts needed anything else and Stark tried to answer, believing the question was directed at him, when he realized that Hogan was working for Potts now. Stark tried to make an awkward joke, but an upset Hogan advised him to stop talking. He and Potts then left the office while Stark spoke to [[Natasha Romanoff|Natalie Rushman]].{{Ref|IM2}}

====Raid of Hammer Industries====
[[File:Happy-Hogan-looks-at-Romanoff.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan watches [[Black Widow|Natalie Rushman]] changing]]
{{Quote|I said stay in the car!"<br>"What are you wearing? Look, I'm not letting you go in alone.|[[Black Widow]] and Happy Hogan|Iron Man 2}}
Hogan became [[Pepper Potts]]' bodyguard when she was named CEO of [[Stark Industries]], and accompanied her to the [[Stark Expo]]. During the [[Battle at Stark Expo]], he was unable to reach Potts and soon approached by [[Natasha Romanoff]], who demanded to get to the [[Hammer Industries Headquarters]] in order to stop [[Ivan Vanko]]'s attack on the Expo. Hogan was wary, but agreed to drive her there. On the way as Romanoff discussed strategy, he could not help but try to look as she changed clothes in the back of the car.
[[File:Happy-Hogan-post-fight-IM2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan fights in [[Hammer Industries]]]]
When they arrived at the facility, Hogan insisted on helping Romanoff with her mission, as he started to fight the first bodyguard they encountered. After a long scuffle, Hogan resorted to using the dirty boxing tactics he had learned from [[Tony Stark]] to knock the guard unconscious. Pleased with his efforts, Hogan called out to Romanoff, only to see she had defeated every other guard in the building. He then stood by Romanoff as she hacked into the [[Hammer Industries]] computer and returned control of the [[War Machine Armor: Mark I|War Machine Armor]] to [[James Rhodes]] so they could join forces and fight back against Vanko.{{Ref|IM2}}

===Head of Security===
====Spying on [[Aldrich Killian]]====
[[File:Happy-Hogan-Pepper-Potts-IM3.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan speaks to [[Pepper Potts]] on his new job]]
{{Quote|Now I got a real job, I'm watching [[Pepper Potts|Pepper]]."<br>"What's going on? Fill me in."<br>"For real? All right, so she's meeting up with this [[Aldrich Killian|scientist]]. Rich guy, handsome. I couldn't make his face at first.|Happy Hogan and [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man 3}}
Hogan soon became very uncomfortable with his role as [[Tony Stark]] aka Iron Man's bodyguard, which he was often ridiculed for. He was subsequently granted a new position as the head of security in the [[Stark Industries Headquarters|corporate headquarters]] of [[Stark Industries]], a role which Hogan took great pride in despite causing staff complaints to rise to a shocking level due to his unrelenting insistence on following protocol. It was in this capacity that Hogan encountered [[Eric Savin]] and his boss, [[Aldrich Killian]], when they visited Stark Industries for a meeting with [[Pepper Potts]]. Hogan checked Killian's credentials and recognized him from the [[Bern 2000]].
[[File:Happy Hogan-Ipad.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan updates [[Tony Stark]] about [[Aldrich Killian]]]]
Hogan then received a call from Stark and struggled to answer the tablet, annoyed at being interrupted at work. He revealed Potts was meeting and possibly flirting with Killian, trying to explain how the latter was showing off his "[[Extremis|big brain]]." The two discussed Hogan's new position and Stark mocked his lack of skill with technology. Hogan planned to follow Killian and Savin, suspicious of their intentions. As the pair said goodbye, Hogan noted that he had barely seen Stark since his friend started working with the [[Avengers]].

Later after arranging for Potts' car, Hogan took a picture of Killian and Savin's vehicle as they drove away in order to run their plates.{{Ref|IM3}}

====[[Destruction of the Chinese Theatre]]====
[[File:Savin Happy.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan confronts [[Eric Savin]]]]
{{Quote|What are you doin', buddy? You out by yourself? A little date night? Watching your favorite chick flick maybe?"<br>"Yeah, a little movie called 'The Party's Over', starring you and your [[Jack Taggart|junkie girlfriend]], and here's the [[Extremis|ticket]].|[[Eric Savin]] and Happy Hogan|Iron Man 3}}
Immediately suspicious, Hogan investigated and later followed [[Eric Savin]] to an exchange with [[Jack Taggart|another man]] at the [[TCL Chinese Theatre]]. He decided to interfere and gather evidence upon noticing some of the man's flesh glowing in an amber hue. After purposefully bumping into the man to make him drop his package, Hogan covertly took one of the [[Extremis|capsules]] the man had been given. Before he could leave, Hogan was confronted by Savin, who tried to steal back the device.
[[File:HappyHoganInjured-IM3.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan after the blast that nearly killed him]]
Hogan attempted to defend himself and punched Savin in the face. Much to his horror though, Savin's wound healed immediately with the same golden glow, and he violently attacked Hogan. Their altercation was interrupted when the other man [[Destruction of the Chinese Theatre|exploded]], killing several people and severely injuring Hogan. He was able to point to the man's dog tags, a vital piece of evidence, before lapsing into unconsciousness; an act that gave [[Tony Stark]] a valuable clue into the cause of the explosion.{{Ref|IM3}}

====Recovery====
[[File:Happy-Hogan-wakes-up.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan finally wakes up inside the [[Cedars-Sinai Hospital|Hospital]]]]
{{Quote|Sunday night's {{WPS|PBS}} ''{{WPS|Downton Abbey}}''. That's his show, he thinks it's elegant. One more thing, make sure everyone wears their badges. He's a stickler for that sort of thing.|[[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man 3}}
Hogan was rendered comatose and admitted to the [[Cedars-Sinai Hospital]]. [[Tony Stark]] stayed by his friend's bedside and asked the nurse to put ''{{WPS|Downton Abbey}}'' on the television, as it was Hogan's favorite show, and ensure that all the staff wore their security badges, since it would annoy Hogan to find out they were not. This incident prompted Stark to publicly threaten the [[Trevor Slattery|Mandarin]], who was responsible for the [[Destruction of the Chinese Theatre|attack]]. Hogan ultimately woke up, days after the explosion, to ''Downton Abbey'' and was attended to by a nurse.{{Ref|IM3}}

===Escorting Peter Parker===
[[File:SMH A Film by Peter Parker 6.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan inside the Stark jet]]
{{Quote|See, Happy is... is hoping to get bumped up to asset management. He was "Forehead of Security", and before that he was just a driver."<br>"That was a private conversation. I don't like joking about this. It was hard for me to talk to you about it.|[[Tony Stark]] and Happy Hogan|Spider-Man: Homecoming}}
In [[2016]], Hogan was still employed at [[Stark Industries]], continuing to be the Head of Security but aspiring to be promoted to asset management. After [[Tony Stark]] recruited [[Peter Parker]] to assist in the [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|fight]] between his team and [[Steve Rogers]]'s team, Hogan was tasked with bringing Parker to [[Germany]]. Hogan picked Parker up and brought him on the Stark private plane.
[[File:SMH Trailer3 15.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan in the hotel room]]
Once in [[Berlin]], Hogan took Parker to their hotel, neighbored with him, and introduced him to the new [[Spider-Man Suit|suit]] designed for him by Stark.{{Ref|SMH}} While staying at the hotel, Hogan was billed for an expensive movie Parker had ordered, and believed the price meant it was an adult film.{{Ref|SMFFH}} Hogan then drove Parker to the [[Leipzig-Halle Airport]] and picked him up afterwards. Later, Hogan had to chastise Parker for being too loud in the hotel room, as the walls were thin.
[[File:SMH A Film by Peter Parker 13.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan dropping off [[Peter Parker]]]]
Hogan then took Parker back to [[New York City]] in the jet plane and met up with Stark, who rode back with them to Parker's apartment complex. Hogan got Parker's suitcase out of the trunk, watched Parker leave, and drove off with Stark.{{Ref|SMH}}

===Worrying about Tony Stark===
{{Quote|You've been in here for two days straight. There's no international incident right now. Nothing that requires the [[Avengers]]' attention. [[Nick Fury]] hasn't called. So what's so important? Why push yourself so ha—"<br>"If I don't push myself, people die. It's that simple.|Happy Hogan and [[Tony Stark]]|Avengers: Infinity War: The Heroes' Journey}}
As time progressed, [[Tony Stark]] got increasingly obsessive over his new [[Iron Man Armor: Mark L|Iron Man armor]], and Hogan got worried that Stark was not eating. He brought fast food for him and tried to get Stark to eat, but Stark could not be convinced. Hogan put the fast food he got on the table, and Stark showed him the schematics for the latest armor he was designing. Hogan again voiced his concern, but Stark simply stated that if he did not push himself, people would die. Hogan remained quiet to allow Stark to concentrate and eventually asked if he had heard from [[Steve Rogers]], so Stark simply said that he had not. Stark asked Hogan for help, and Hogan asked about [[Peter Parker]], mentioning that he had left ten voicemails for Hogan the previous day. Stark tested his gauntlet, which crushed a cinder block into ash, and said it needed work. Hogan sarcastically agreed, so the two went for a walk, where Stark told Hogan that he wanted to keep track of the [[Avengers]] more so they could be prepared for future threats. They briefly talked about Stark's attempt to lift [[Mjølnir]], when Stark asked Hogan to contact whomever he could. Hogan commented on how weird the world was, and Stark agreed, noting how much more advanced [[Asgard]]ian technology was and wanting to match their level.

Later that day, Hogan contacted Stark to remind him of the satellite launch which Stark was meant to attend with [[Maria Hill]]. While driving Stark to the launch, Hogan asked why Stark was suddenly interested in space, so Stark explained that the satellite would launch nano-satellites into space to detect anything. Hogan watched the launch with Stark and Hill, but was unimpressed. Stark told Hill that the nano-satellites would take a month to reach their positions, and the two discussed Stark's hope of not finding anything.{{Ref|AIWTHJ}}

===Asset Management===
====Monitoring Spider-Man====
[[File:HHoganGetACallAgainFromPParker.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan answers a phone call from [[Peter Parker]]]]
{{Quote|Look, just stay away from anything too dangerous. I'm responsible for making sure you're responsible, okay?|Happy Hogan to [[Spider-Man]]|Spider-Man: Homecoming}}
Two months later, Hogan had been promoted to asset management as requested and was assigned to oversee the removal of all items and technology from [[Avengers Tower]] after Stark sold the building to move to the [[Avengers Compound]] in upstate [[New York]]. Hogan was also Parker's primary contact as he started his crime-fighting career, and duly relayed all of Parker's messages to Stark.{{Ref|SMH}}

Soon after, Hogan went to the Compound on a weekend and found Stark monitoring his [[Stark Industries Satellite|nano-satellites]] alone. He gave Stark takeout and explained that he felt Stark needed company. He told Stark that after talking to Parker, he believed the young hero's heart to be in the right place. The pair watched the monitor together, and Hogan used his fork to emulate the sound of the satellites pinging, which Stark and Hogan both laughed at. Stark stepped outside to take a call, and Hogan tried on the gauntlet to one of Stark's [[:Category:Iron Man Armors|Iron Man armors]], quickly hiding them behind his back as Stark returned. Stark expressed surprise that Hogan waited as long as he did to try them on and agreed with Hogan that they were heavier than they appeared.{{Ref|AIWTHJ}}

====[[Hijacking of the Stark Cargo Plane]]====
[[File:SMH Trailer3 25.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan's team loading the [[Stark Cargo Plane]]]]
{{Quote|We just gotta load [[Iron Man|Tony]]'s old [[Hulkbuster]] armor, prototype for [[Steve Rogers|Cap]]'s new [[Captain America's Shield|shield]] and the Meg..me..megin... [[Thor]]'s [[Megingjörð|magic belt]].|Happy Hogan|Spider-Man: Homecoming}}
On moving day, Hogan oversaw the loading of all of the items due to be moved onto the [[Stark Cargo Plane|cargo plane]]. He was contacted by Parker's friend [[Ned Leeds]], who tried to warn him that the plane was in danger, but he brushed off the warning. After seeing it off, the plane was [[Hijacking of the Stark Cargo Plane|hijacked]] by [[Vulture]] and subsequently crashed on [[Coney Island]] after Spider-Man intervened.
[[File:Happy Vulture.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan finds [[Vulture]]]]
Hogan accompanied the [[FBI]] to the crash site where they found Toomes webbed and restrained on the side of a car, with a note from [[Spider-Man]] reading: "Found the Flying Vulture Guy. P.S. Sorry about your [[Stark Cargo Plane|plane]]." Hogan watched as the federal agents arrested Toomes for his failed robbery, with Hogan earning a newfound respect and admiration for Spider-Man.{{Ref|SMH}}

====Parker's Rejection====
[[File:Happy Hogan Visits Peter in a High School Washroom.PNG|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan talks to [[Peter Parker]] in private]]
{{Quote|I really owe you one. I don't know what I would do without this job.|Happy Hogan to [[Peter Parker]]|Spider-Man: Homecoming}}
Days later, Hogan appeared at Parker's [[Midtown School of Science and Technology|school]] to personally apologize for not listening to his warnings, and to thank him for saving his job. He then took Parker on a ride to the [[Avengers Compound]] where [[Tony Stark]] intended to announce [[Spider-Man]] to the world as the newest official member of the [[Avengers]]. However, Parker declined the invitation and left the building to wait in the car for a ride home. As he left, Hogan expressed to Stark that Parker was a "good kid."
[[File:Happy Hogan (Carrying This Since 2008).png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan provides a ring for [[Tony Stark]]]]
[[Pepper Potts]] then reminded Hogan and Stark that there was a room full of press expecting an announcement; Stark asked Hogan if he was still carrying an engagement ring, and intended to give them it. However, Potts was somewhat confused by the tactic and assured the two that she would think of something better. Despite Potts' word, Hogan tossed the ring to Stark as a last-case measure.{{Ref|SMH}} 

====Interviewing Wade Wilson====
[[File:Happy Hogan.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan having a meeting with [[Wade Wilson]]]]
{{Quote|I mean, people look up to us. Kids look up to us."<br>"I'm sorry, us? I wasn't aware that you were an [[Avengers|Avenger]]."<br>"Avengers adjacent, technically.|Happy Hogan and [[Wade Wilson]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
On [[2018|March 14, 2018]], Hogan interviewed [[Wade Wilson]] at the [[Avengers Compound]]. When Hogan asked Wilson what he was wanting, he answered that he wanted to matter, although Wilson wondered if [[Tony Stark]] would be joining them. Hogan explained that he was in charge of the meeting, as Stark was too busy for entry-level matters. Wilson was confused, thinking that Hogan was only Stark's chauffeur, so Hogan explained that he started as Stark's driver and moved up to head of security.
[[File:Wilson and Hogan.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan passes on [[Wade Wilson]]'s application]]
Hogan continued the interview, asking about Wilson's team experience in {{WPS|X-Force#Film|X-Force}}, which did not give Hogan confidence in Wilson. Seeing the interview failing, Wilson expressed his desire to join the [[Avengers]], saying he needed it. Hogan told Wilson that the Avengers did what they do because others needed them, and included himself as part of the team, which Wilson questioned. Hogan then ended the interview, rejecting Wilson's application, and he told him to find a place where he can thrive.{{Ref|DW}} Two months later, the [[Snap]] occurred, wiping out half of all humanity, although Hogan survived.{{Ref|AE}}

====Tony Stark's Funeral====
[[File:Stark's final message 4.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan watches [[Tony Stark]]'s final message]]
{{Quote|I'll get you all the cheeseburgers you want.|Happy Hogan to [[Morgan Stark]]|Avengers: Endgame}}
In [[2023]], Hogan, along with [[Pepper Potts]], [[Morgan Stark]], [[James Rhodes]], [[Steve Rogers]], [[Bruce Banner]], [[Clint Barton]] and [[Thor]] watched [[Tony Stark]]'s recording at the [[Stark Eco-Compound]] that he made in preparation for the possibility that he would not survive the [[Time Heist|mission]].
[[File:Peter Parker & Steve Rogers.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan and [[James Rhodes]] comfort each other]]
Hogan then went outside to the lake, where the rest of the [[Avengers]] and their allies were standing. He and Rhodes comforted each other, both being very close to Stark, as they watched Potts and Morgan place Stark's [[Arc Reactor]] on the lake.
[[File:Happy Hogan & Morgan Stark.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan sitting down with [[Morgan Stark]]]]
Afterwards, Hogan sat with Morgan by the house and asked her if she was hungry. She replied that she wanted cheeseburgers. An emotional Hogan smiled, telling her that her father liked cheeseburgers as well, and promised to get her all the cheeseburgers she wanted. Following this, Hogan was given possession of [[Dum-E]].{{Ref|AE}}

===[[Mysterio's Masquerade]]===
====Flirting with May Parker====
[[File:Spider-ManFarFromHomeTeaserTrailer6.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan hands [[May Parker]] a large check]]
{{Quote|If you don't talk to [[Talos|him]], then I have to talk. I don't wanna talk to him."<br>"Why don't you wanna talk to him?"<br>"Because I'm scared. Just answer the phone.|Happy Hogan and [[Peter Parker]]|Spider-Man: Far From Home}}
In [[2024]], Hogan went to a [[Salvation Army|charity event]] for people displaced by the [[Blip]] in [[New York City]] to see [[Peter Parker]]. When Hogan arrived, he was greeted by Parker and [[May Parker]]. He then presented May with a large check from [[Pepper Potts]] before he began flirting with May by complimenting her about her hair and asking her about her new dress, to which she responded to commenting about his beard.
[[File:Spider-ManFarFromHomeTeaserTrailer8.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan flirting with [[May Parker]]]]
When May left, Parker asked Hogan what happened, but he ignored him and told him that [[Talos|Nick Fury]] was calling him. Hogan told Parker that Fury calls superheroes for any activities. When Parker's phone started ringing, Hogan told Parker that that was Fury calling him, but he reluctantly refused to speak to him but told Parker to answer the phone or else he will have to.
[[File:SMFarFromHomeTrailer15.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan talks about [[Talos|Nick Fury]]'s calls]]
When Parker hung up on Fury, Hogan freaked out and strongly advised against "ghosting" Fury. Parker then told Hogan that he had to go as he noticed the crowd of people calling him backstage. He promised Hogan that he'll call Fury later on. Once Parker left, Hogan immediately received a call from Fury, whom he tried to reassure that Parker was not "ghosting" him.{{Ref|SMFFH}}

====Helping at Salvation Army====
[[File:Happy Hogan (Spider-Man FFH).png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan eating [[May Parker]]'s lunch]]
{{Quote|I'm glad you're having a good time. Don’t worry. I'm really taking care of your [[May Parker|aunt]].|Happy Hogan to [[Peter Parker]]|Spider-Man: Far From Home}}
Later, after Parker left for a school trip to Europe, Hogan and May began a momentarily relationship. One day, while the two were at a restaurant, May called Parker to ask him about the recent [[battle in the Grand Canal]]. As she did this, Happy ate May's food, to which she told him not to eat her lunch.
[[File:Happy (SMFFH).png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan says hello to [[Peter Parker]]]]
May then briefly gave the call to Hogan so he could say hi to Parker, though he didn't really want to say hi to him, he did it anyway. Hogan then told a suspicious Parker that he was simply helping May and taking care of her, though Parker did not believe it.{{Ref|SMFFH}}

====Advising Peter Parker====
[[File:Happy Parker Netherlands.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan rescues [[Peter Parker]]]]
{{Quote|You're not [[Iron Man]]. You're never gonna be Iron Man. Nobody could live up to Tony. Not even Tony. Tony was my best friend. And he was a mess. He second-guessed everything he did; he was all over the place. The one thing that he did that he didn't second-guess was picking you.|Happy Hogan to [[Peter Parker]]|Spider-Man: Far From Home}}
Days later, Hogan was called by [[Peter Parker]], who told Hogan to pick him up in the [[Netherlands]] as he was stranded there. Once he arrived at Parker's location in a [[Stark Industries Private Jet]], Parker asked if he was really Hogan, much to his confusion. Parker then demanded Hogan to prove he's himself by telling him something only the real Happy would know. Hogan then proved this by revealing that he knew about Parker renting a presumably R-rated movie while at the hotel in [[Germany]] in [[2016]]. Parker then hugged Hogan, who asked for an explanation on what was happening with him.
[[File:SMFarFromHomeTrailer5.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan and [[Peter Parker]] discuss [[Tony Stark]]]]
Upon entering the plane, Parker told him that he was nearly killed by [[Quentin Beck]], an illusionist who was using illusions of [[Elementals|powerful creatures]] to make the world think he was a new hero, and who fooled Parker into giving him [[E.D.I.T.H.]], an AI created by [[Tony Stark]] with control over hundreds of drones, as well as into revealing who of Parker's friends know about his plot. As Hogan gave first aid to Parker, the latter yelled at Hogan on how he failed to stop Beck's plan. After Parker calmed down and opened up about how he feels unable to live up to Stark's legacy, Hogan comforted Peter by telling him that not even Stark could live up to his own legacy, but revealed that picking Parker as his protégé was the only decision Stark never regretted or second-guessed. Hogan felt that Stark wouldn't have sacrificed himself if he didn't know that Parker would survive to continue his work.
[[File:SMFarFromHomeTrailer55.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan watches [[Peter Parker]] making his suit]]
A motivated Parker then instructed Hogan to give him his phone so he could know where Beck's plan was going to happen, which he discovered was in [[London]]. Hogan then proudly watched as Peter created a new Spider-Man suit with Stark technology, before playing [[AC/DC]]'s "{{WPS|Back in Black}}," and piloting the plane. Before fighting Beck, Hogan tried to sent [[Talos|Nick Fury]] a coded message warning him of Beck's deception, but, unbeknownst to Hogan, Fury didn't realize it was a message. Hogan then asked Parker about his battle plan, which he explained to Hogan, before asking Hogan to give [[Michelle Jones]] a Black Dahlia necklace he bought for her in case Parker was killed-in-action.{{Ref|SMFFH}}

====[[Battle of London]]====
[[File:Far From Home 60.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan sees [[Peter Parker]] jump off the plane]]
{{Quote|I work with [[Spider-Man]], okay? You got to get on that [[Stark Industries Private Jet|jet]]."<br>"You work for Spider-Man?"<br>"I work ''with'' Spider-Man, not ''for'' Spider-Man!|Happy Hogan and [[Flash Thompson]]|Spider-Man: Far From Home}}
Upon arriving in [[London]], Hogan saw the illusion that [[Mysterio]]'s drones generated and was shocked by its realism and even asked Parker if it's really fake, which he confirmed. Before jumping off the plane in his new suit, Parker told Hogan that they would have to talk about his and May's relationship later.
[[File:SMFarFromHomeTrailer63.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan finds [[Peter Parker]]'s classmates]]
After landing the plane, Hogan found Parker's friends, [[Ned Leeds]], [[Michelle Jones]], [[Betty Brant]], and [[Flash Thompson]], through Thompson's social media videos. He then introduced himself to them and told them to come with him. However, one of the [[E.D.I.T.H.|drones]] destroyed their plane in order to prevent them from escaping.
[[File:Happy running .jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan running from the [[E.D.I.T.H.|drones]]]]
Hogan then instructed the students to hide inside the vault of the Royal Crown Jewels. While entering the vault, Hogan and the kids were forced to escape from a drone that followed them. As Hogan and the kids entered the vault, he desperately tried to throw a shield at the drone, only to fail, causing him to wonder how [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] could do it with [[Captain America's Shield|his own shield]].
[[File:Happy Students.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan braces for the [[E.D.I.T.H.|drones]]]]
Once inside, as the drone started shooting missiles at the vault, Hogan and the kids, believing it to be their final moments, openly admitted several of their secrets. Hogan confessed that he was in love with Spider-Man's aunt, much to Jones, Leeds, Brant, and Thompson's surprise. Once the shooting ended, Hogan and the kids realized that Parker had been successful in stopping the drones and left the vault.{{Ref|SMFFH}}

===Spider-Man Controversy===
====Returning to New York====
[[File:Happy Far From Home .jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan speaks with [[May Parker|May]] and [[Peter Parker]]]]
{{Quote|Are you dating?"<br>"Not really."<br>"Yes.|[[Peter Parker]], [[May Parker]], and Happy Hogan|Spider-Man: Far From Home}}
Back in [[New York City]], Hogan met with [[May Parker|May]] at the [[Parker Residence]] and [[Peter Parker]] demanded an explanation from them about their relationship. May described it as a fling, whereas Hogan said that he thought they had a long-term connection. Parker would leave to go on his own date while leaving Hogan and May alone.{{Ref|SMFFH}}
[[File:Happy unhappy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan disappointed that [[May Parker]] broke up with him]]
They would later get intimate, but citing boundaries, May quickly decided to break off the relationship, much to Hogan's distress. As she led him out the door of the apartment, they heard a noise coming from within. Despite May telling him it was okay, Hogan came back inside and went to where the noise came from, opening a bedroom door seeing Parker and [[Michelle Jones]], having entered through Parker's bedroom window.
[[File:Happy Hogan (No Way Home).png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan sees [[Peter Parker]] and [[Michelle Jones]]]]
Noticing that Parker was undressed, Hogan stepped back in surprise and waited until May came and saw to him. Hogan then went with them into the living room and Parker demanded them explain their relationship, before they saw on the television that [[NY1]] was reporting on Parker's identity as Spider-Man. [[WLGJ]] helicopters then were seen hovering and they realized that the footage was live. Parker then used his [[Web-Shooters]] to close the windows, but opened one again to show May that the helicopters were outside their building.{{Ref|SMNWH}}

===Legal Troubles===
====Meeting with Matt Murdock====
[[File:Happy Hogan (2024).png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan sees his picture on the television]]
{{Quote|I could say under advisement of counsel, I refuse to answer the question respectfully because I... the answer could incriminate me. There's a saying in ''{{WPS|Goodfellas}}''. What did they say in ''Goodfellas''?|Happy Hogan to [[Matt Murdock]]|Spider-Man: No Way Home}}
Hogan watched as [[NY1]] continued stating that the [[United States Department of Damage Control]] had taken charge of the investigation and that due to the [[Stark Industries Combat Drones|drones]] being made by [[Stark Industries]], Hogan would be investigated, with Hogan commenting on the picture they chose to use for him. Hogan then left the [[Parker Residence]] to let [[Peter Parker]] and [[May Parker]] have time together.
[[File:Happy Hogan talks to Matt Murdock.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan speaks with [[Matt Murdock]]]]
A few days later, Hogan returned to the apartment to be present for the meeting with Parker, May, and Parker's lawyer, [[Matt Murdock]]. Murdock told Parker he was able to clear him of the legal charges, cut the things weren't all the way good yet. He then told Hogan that he would be investigated due to his status in Stark Industries, and advised he seek immediate legal protection.{{Ref|SMNWH}}

====Living with the Parkers====
[[File:Happy (NWH).png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan welcomes [[May Parker|May]] and [[Peter Parker]] into his [[Happy Hogan's Condominium|condominium]]]]
{{Quote|Welcome to the [[Happy Hogan's Condominium|spiritual oasis]]. You like ''{{WPS|Donkey Kong Jr.}}''?|Happy Hogan to [[Peter Parker]] and [[May Parker]]|Spider-Man: No Way Home}}
Following this, [[May Parker]] stated they needed a safer place to live and Hogan offered them to stay at his [[Happy Hogan's Condominium|condominium]] on [[New York City|Long Island]]. Hogan welcomed May and Parker to his condominium and asked Parker if he liked Donkey Kong, while [[Dum-E]] greeted them. After they got settled in, Hogan gave his bed to May and chose to sleep in a lounge chair in his living room.
[[File:Happy Hogan Sleeping.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan trying to sleep]]
One night, [[Peter Parker]], who was designated to sleep on the couch, was video-calling [[Michelle Jones]] and became too loud in their conversation. Irritated, Hogan told Peter to end the call so he could get some sleep.{{Ref|SMNWH}}

===[[Spider-Man Multiversal Crisis]]===
====Interrogated by Damage Control====
[[File:Happy Hogan & Matt Murdock.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan speaks with [[Matt Murdock]]]]
{{Quote|Happy, stop sweating."<br>"How do you do that?|[[Matt Murdock]] and Happy Hogan|Spider-Man: No Way Home}}
As he was being investigated for the [[Stark Industries Combat Drones]] used during the [[Battle of London]], Hogan hired [[Matt Murdock]] to be his attorney. Murdock represented Hogan during an interrogation with the [[United States Department of Damage Control]]. However, Hogan was too nervous and distracted to concentrate on the questions, as he witnessed a [[Green Goblin|group]] [[Sandman|of]] [[Electro|suspicious]] [[Doctor Octopus|men]] entering his [[Happy Hogan's Condominium|apartment]], invited by [[Peter Parker]] and [[May Parker]]. Aware that Hogan had started sweating, Murdock urged him to stop, prompting Hogan to ask how he could do that.{{Ref|SMNWHTMFSV}}

====[[Escape from Spider-Man|Condo Destruction]]====
[[File:HappyAsksSinisterFive.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan calls [[Peter Parker]]]]
{{Quote|I accessed my doorbell camera... Who are those guys, huh? Is [[Doctor Octopus|that]] a cyborg? You bring a cyborg with [[Doctor Octopus' Tentacles|robot legs]] into my [[Happy Hogan's Condominium|house]]? [[Sandman|One]] of the guys was made of mud? What’s going on? Call me back.|Happy Hogan to [[Peter Parker]]'s voicemail|Spider-Man: No Way Home}}
Hogan drove back from the deposition and called [[Peter Parker]] from his vehicle. Upon being put to voicemail, Hogan left a message inquiring as to why he had brought strange men, including one with [[Doctor Octopus|robot legs]] and a [[Sandman|man made of mud]], into his apartment. Hogan then asked Parker to call him back before disconnecting the call.
[[File:Spider-Man NWH trailer 101.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan realizes [[May Parker]] has been killed]]
Hogan arrived at his condominium, only to find it destroyed with smoke and fires around the area. He rolled down his passenger side window and saw Parker, who was emotional and battle weary, holding onto May's lifeless body. Hogan became distraught at what had happened.
[[File:Happy Hogan arrested.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan is arrested by [[Damage Control]]]]
However, he was then forcibly taken out of his car by the [[United States Department of Damage Control]] agents on the scene. As he was being taken into custody, Hogan yelled out to Parker to run before Damage Control's SWAT team began to open fire.{{Ref|SMNWH}}
{{Clear}}

====Losing May====
[[File:Happy Hogan (December 2024).png|{{AltFloat}}|Hogan visiting [[May Parker]]'s grave]]
{{Quote|I lost a [[Tony Stark|good friend]] a while back, felt like this. Hurts because they're gone, and then, it hurts all over again because you remember what they stood for, and you wonder... is all that gone, too?|Happy Hogan to [[Peter Parker]]|Spider-Man: No Way Home}}
Shortly afterwards, Hogan, along with the rest of his universe, had his memory of [[Peter Parker]] erased. In December, he went solemnly to [[May Parker]]'s gravesite and saw a [[Peter Parker|young man]] there as well and asked how he knew May. He replied it was due to [[Spider-Man]], in which Hogan said the same for him. He then recalled losing [[Tony Stark]] a year ago, saying that it felt the same losing May, although a little different. The young man reassured him that he knew things would get better. He and the young man then exchanged their goodbyes and wished each other well.{{Ref|SMNWH}}

==Abilities==
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved by Wiki-Projects with the media released as of the end of 2021. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. -->
*'''Combatant''': [[File:Happy Hogan Dirty Boxing.png|thumb|250px|Hogan fighting against a security guard]] Hogan was a former professional boxer and occasionally sparred with [[Tony Stark]]. Hogan learned to use mixed martial arts from his sparring with Stark and, with considerable effort, was able to defeat a professional security guard of [[Hammer Industries]]. Hogan was also able to cause enough damage to [[Eric Savin]]'s face with just one punch to the point where the latter had to heal the damage for several seconds with his [[Extremis]] powers.
*'''Pilot''': Hogan is a capable pilot able to fly the [[Stark Industries Private Jet]], having it at his disposal when having to rescue [[Peter Parker]] at the [[Netherlands]].

==Equipment==
===Vehicles===
*'''{{WPS|Rolls-Royce Phantom VII}}''': One of [[Iron Man|Tony Stark]]'s luxury cars, which Happy drove to chauffeur Stark and [[Pepper Potts]]. In [[Monaco]], it was sliced in half by [[Whiplash]]'s [[Whiplash Armor: Mark I|electrical whips]].
*'''[[Stark Industries Private Jet]]''': Happy used the Stark Industries Private Jet to assist Peter Parker after he became stranded in the Netherlands. After he succeeded, Hogan would then fly Parker to London as he constructed a new Spider-Man suit aboard the jet. Shortly after landing, Hogan attempted to fly Parker's friends away to safety within the jet, but it was destroyed by drones before they could board.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Stark Industries Headquarters]]''': Hogan provided security at [[Stark Industries]]' headquarters, where he did what he could to keep the company and his boss, [[Tony Stark]], safe.
*'''[[Tony Stark's Mansion]]''': As Tony Stark's bodyguard, Happy Hogan spent a great deal of time at Tony Stark's mansion. Occasionally, he would spar with Stark in his boxing ring.
*'''[[Cedars-Sinai Hospital]]''': After receiving mortal injuries at the hands of Eric Savin's actions, Hogan slipped into a coma and was kept at the Cedars-Sinai Hospital. Tony Stark visited Hogan and ensured the television show ''Downton Abbey'' be played for Hogan should he wake up. Ultimately, Hogan pulled through and watched the show on television as he recovered.
*'''[[Avengers Tower]]''': Hogan packed Avengers Tower on [[Tony Stark]]'s behalf following the sale of the building.
*'''[[Avengers Compound]]''': Much like Tony Stark's mansion, Hogan spent a lot of time at the Avengers Compound in the company of Stark. He apparently spent enough time at the compound to become familiar with the behaviour of its inhabitants, as Hogan commented on Vision's habit of phasing through walls into people's rooms unannounced.
*'''[[Stark Eco-Compound]]''': Following the death of [[Tony Stark]], Hogan went to Stark's house and watched a recording left by Stark. He attended Stark's funeral and stayed with his [[Morgan Stark|daughter]], offering her cheeseburgers.
*'''[[Parker Residence]]''': Hogan often visited the residence of Peter and May Parker, mostly to visit the latter during their brief fling. 
*'''[[Happy Hogan's Condominium]]''': Happy Hogan offered to let Peter and May Parker stay at his apartment in order to hide from the backlash of the public believing Spider-Man, and thus Peter Parker, to be a murderer. Peter eventually used Hogan's apartment as a temporary base, where he could develop individual cures for interdimensional visitors. However, this plan ultimately failed and a battle ensued, damaging Hogan's apartment and several other floors of the building. Hogan later left Peter a voicemail message, asking him who the villains were, confused as to why Peter had let them in.

